-- RoleAssignments: Table: RoleAssignments. The temporal history of ntwf:filledBy. Part IV (Change Management) requires that when a filledBy triple is updated the old triple is NOT deleted — it is timestamped and retained, or replaced with a versioned triple carrying a validity period. Each row is one filledBy binding with a ValidFrom / ValidTo validity period and the reason for the change, so that 'which agent was executing this step on March 1, 2026?' is answerable from the graph. The current binding on Roles.FilledBy* is the row whose ValidTo is blank (IsCurrent = TRUE); closed rows preserve provenance and chain of custody. This is the relational equivalent of Part IV's named-graph / versioned-triple retention practice.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
